name: Jiwan Coffee & Things Bali
address: 86QX+FR9, Jl. Sedap Malam No.100x, Kesiman, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
I recently visited Jiwan Coffee & Things in Bali, and it turned out to be a delightful spot for a coffee fix and more. The quality of the coffee was decent, delivering a satisfying pick-me-up to kickstart the day.

What truly sets Jiwan Coffee & Things apart is its charming interior design. The second level, though open-air, provides a nice ambiance, but it can get quite hot during the day. However, the real surprise was discovering the secret level 3, offering a serene view of the rice paddy fields. It's a hidden gem that adds a unique touch to the overall experience.

I decided to sample some of the food offerings as well. While the pasta was okay, it was the rice dishes that truly stood out. The flavors were delightful, and the quality of the rice was exceptional. It's always a pleasure to find a place that excels in the basics.

In terms of pricing, Jiwan Coffee & Things offers good value for money, making it a very affordable option for a meal or a coffee break. The affordability combined with the nice ambiance and decent quality of food and coffee make it a must-visit for those looking for a relaxed setting to unwind.

Overall, Jiwan Coffee & Things is a lovely place to enjoy a cup of coffee, savor a meal, and take in the peaceful surroundings. If you find yourself in Bali and in need of a cozy spot to unwind, Jiwan Coffee & Things is definitely worth checking out.

name: Mai Mesaree Villa
address: Sedap Malam Streat, No:88, Kesiman, Denpasar, Bali Bali, Sumerta Kelod, East Denpasar, Denpasar City, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
I recently stayed here which left me feeling incredibly disappointed and regretful. Despite the photos provided in the listing, the reality of the accommodation was far from what I was expecting.

Firstly, the apartment itself was not well-maintained as the photos had led me to believe.  It was clear that the space had not been properly cleaned or maintained before our arrival.

But what really upset me was the pool. The photos showed a sparkling white-blue oasis, but in reality, the pool wall was in terrible condition. It was covered in grime and dirt, and there were even cracks in the wall

To make matters worse, there was no one at the reception the property could look fancy but turned out creepy as they don't maintenance their property, and they did not address my complaints about the apartment and pool. This made me feel like they were not concerned about providing a quality experience for their guest.

Overall, I am deeply disappointed by my experience at this Airbnb.
